(58393, '52F271C2-43F9-4BE0-9716-6B47A4A756B4', 'Thanks love for reflecting back to me what felt immensely painful and what made me nearly walk away from us. I️ needed to hear it in writing to be sure you really did internalize what got me to a breaking point. Thank you for this gift. I️ feel heard and seen through this acknowledgment. While I’m not in the position to align on these specific values related to non monogamy, I️ do hope to one day be in a better place to accept the places where we can push each other to be the best versions of ourselves. We’ve learned through this experience that relentless pushing, yelling our positions, speaking in patronizing and condensing ways, and ultimately a death threat lead us to the worst downward relationship spiral I️ have ever experienced. I️ hope as we rebuild slowly, we will find ways in the years ahead to push each other with love and tenderness. I️ have always admired, respected, and appreciated your insights and values about me and how you want to operate in the world. It will take time and a lot more good will before we get there but that is my vision and dream for us. I married you because we do align on so much of what we want for ourselves and for the world around us. For now, we just need a lot of wins to compensate for a few months of the nastiness and negativity that has drained us both. I️ very much intend to get to your pain. I️ have tried for two years and will continue to do everything I️ can, with the exception of giving up these very occasional connections. I️ know you aren’t ok with them but I️ appreciate your acceptance of them. I️ know it’s hard and you are stretching yourself. That means a lot. Thank you for understanding that these needs aren’t a punch at you, they are just fuel for me. I️ hope that acceptance of me really truly means that our home can be a loving place and that I️ am not coming home to hostility if I️ spend an evening having dinner with Ken. If you need space I️ understand that. But I️’m going to ask you to be kind. That’s the base for acceptance. I️ have many many sides to me. I️ am a ceo, a mom, a community builder, a lover of connection and friendship, a flirt, a exerciser, a podcast consumer, a lover of ideas, an explorer, and a relentless champion of making the world a more loving place with more equality. My connection to men is one small slice of me. It’s a significant one, but it’s paltry in comparison to where I️ spend the bulk of my time and energy. I️ hope that offers some perspective on all the places in the world we can connect and align. I️ know this was a long note with many threads. Sorry for the many layers here but I️ wanted to put it all in writing somewhere and your note inspired me. I️ have been writing versions of this in my head on the 7 rounds of marin these last two days. Thanks for helping to turn this around from rock bottom. We will build this back up together. I️’m with you and I️ love you dearly. ', '688444896872664960', '688445922656175104', 0, 'Nitzan', 'David', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'E:nwdave@b-zb.com', '+19172390518', '2022-10-25T19:41:36.872665'),
